<div class="processing-stat">
                    <span class="processing-number remaining" id="remainingCount">15</span>
                    <div>Remaining</div>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div style="text-align: center; margin: 20px 0;" id="simulatorControls">
                <button class="btn btn-secondary" onclick="resetSimulator()">Reset Practice</button>
                <button class="btn btn-success" onclick="showProcessingTips()" style="margin-left: 10px;">Get Processing Tips</button>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Slide 5: Daily Processing Ritual -->
        <div class="slide" id="slide5">
            <h2>‚è∞ Your Daily Processing Ritual</h2>
            
            <div class="insight-box">
                <h3>The 20-Minute Transformation</h3>
                <p style="font-size: 1.1em;">
                    Research shows that 20 minutes of focused email processing is more effective than checking email sporadically throughout the day. Here's your exact daily ritual:
                </p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="timer-widget">
                <h3>üéØ Processing Timer</h3>
                <div class="timer-display" id="timerDisplay">20:00</div>
                <p>Use this timer for your daily processing sessions</p>
                
                <div class="timer-controls">
                    <button class="btn" onclick="startTimer()">Start Session</button>
                    <button class="btn btn-secondary" onclick="pauseTimer()">Pause</button>
                    <button class="btn btn-secondary" onclick="resetTimer()">Reset</button>
                </div>
                
                <div id="timerStatus" style="margin-top: 15px; font-size: 1.1em; font-weight: bold;">
                    Ready to start your processing session
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="step-guide">
                <div class="step-item" id="step1">
                    <h4>Prepare Your Environment</h4>
                    <ul style="margin: 10px 0 10px 20px;">
                        <li>Close all other applications and browser tabs</li>
                        <li>Turn off notifications (phone on silent)</li>
                        <li>Have your calendar open for scheduling</li>
                        <li>Set your timer for 20 minutes</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p><strong>Time Investment:</strong> 2 minutes</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="step-item" id="step2">
                    <h4>Process Top to Bottom</h4>
                    <ul style="margin: 10px 0 10px 20px;">
                        <li>Start with the oldest email (top of list)</li>
                        <li>Process one email completely before moving to next</li>
                        <li>Never return an email to the inbox</li>
                        <li>Apply 4 D's framework to each email</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p><strong>Time Investment:</strong> 15 minutes</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="step-item" id="step3">
                    <h4>Process to Zero or Time</h4>
                    <ul style="margin: 10px 0 10px 20px;">
                        <li>Continue until inbox is empty OR timer rings</li>
                        <li>If time runs out, schedule next session</li>
                        <li>Mark your stopping point for next session</li>
                        <li>Never leave emails "half-processed"</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p><strong>Time Investment:</strong> Until completion</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="step-item" id="step4">
                    <h4>Quick Review and Plan</h4>
                    <ul style="margin: 10px 0 10px 20px;">
                        <li>Review flagged items and due dates</li>
                        <li>Check calendar for next day's appointments</li>
                        <li>Plan your next processing session</li>
                        <li>Feel the satisfaction of an empty inbox!</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p><strong>Time Investment:</strong> 3 minutes</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="interactive-section">
                <h3>üïê Optimal Processing Times</h3>
                <p style="margin-bottom: 15px;">Choose processing times that work with your natural energy and schedule:</p>
                
                <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr)); gap: 15px;">
                    <div style="background: #f0f9ff; padding: 15px; border-radius: 8px; border-left: 5px solid #3b82f6;">
                        <h4>üåÖ Early Morning (7-9 AM)</h4>
                        <p><strong>Best for:</strong> High energy, few interruptions, sets positive tone for day</p>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div style="background: #f0fdf4; padding: 15px; border-radius: 8px; border-left: 5px solid #10b981;">
                        <h4>üçΩÔ∏è Post-Lunch (1-2 PM)</h4>
                        <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Natural energy dip, routine task perfect for this time</p>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div style="background: #fef5e7; padding: 15px; border-radius: 8px; border-left: 5px solid #f59e0b;">
                        <h4>üåÜ End of Day (4-5 PM)</h4>
                        <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Clearing the deck, preparing for tomorrow, closure</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Slide 6: Setting Up Outlook for Processing -->
        <div class="slide" id="slide6">
            <h2>‚öôÔ∏è Configure Outlook for Optimal Processing</h2>
            
            <div class="insight-box">
                <h3>Setup = Success</h3>
                <p>The right Outlook configuration makes processing effortless. Let's optimize your setup for maximum efficiency.</p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="interactive-section">
                <h3>üìß Essential Outlook Settings</h3>
                <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">Follow this checklist to configure Outlook for GTD processing:</p>
                
                <div class="step-guide">
                    <div class="step-item" onclick="toggleStep(this)">
                        <h4>Turn Off Desktop Notifications</h4>
                        <p>File ‚Üí Options ‚Üí Mail ‚Üí Message arrival ‚Üí Uncheck all notification options</p>
                        <div style="background: #f8f9fa; padding: 10px; border-radius: 5px; margin: 10px 0; font-size: 0.9em;">
                            <strong>Why:</strong> Notifications break your focus and create reactive email checking habits.
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="step-item" onclick="toggleStep(this)">
                        <h4>Set Up Reading Pane</h4>
                        <p>View ‚Üí Reading Pane ‚Üí Right (or Bottom if you prefer)</p>
                        <div style="background: #f8f9fa; padding: 10px; border-radius: 5px; margin: 10px 0; font-size: 0.9em;">
                            <strong>Why:</strong> See email content without double-clicking, speeds up processing.
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="step-item" onclick="toggleStep(this)">
                        <h4>Create Quick Steps</h4>
                        <p>Home ‚Üí Quick Steps ‚Üí Create New ‚Üí Set up Delete & Archive actions</p>
                        <div style="background: #f8f9fa; padding: 10px; border-radius: 5px; margin: 10px 0; font-size: 0.9em;">
                            <strong>Why:</strong> One-click processing for common actions saves time and reduces decision fatigue.
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="step-item" onclick="toggleStep(this)">
                        <h4>Configure Send/Receive Groups</h4>
                        <p>Send/Receive ‚Üí Send/Receive Groups ‚Üí Define Send/Receive Groups</p>
                        <div style="background: #f8f9fa; padding: 10px; border-radius: 5px; margin: 10px 0; font-size: 0.9em;">
                            <strong>Why:</strong> Control when emails arrive instead of constant interruption.
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="step-item" onclick="toggleStep(this)">
                        <h4>Set Up Categories</h4>
                        <p>Home ‚Üí Categorize ‚Üí All Categories ‚Üí Create @Calls, @Computer, @Meetings, @Waiting</p>
                        <div style="background: #f8f9fa; padding: 10px; border-radius: 5px; margin: 10px 0; font-size: 0.9em;">
                            <strong>Why:</strong> GTD contexts help you see what actions you can take right now.
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="rule-examples">
                <div class="rule-card">
                    <div class="rule-title">üéØ Quick Steps Setup</div>
                    <div class="rule-description">Create these Quick Steps for faster processing:</div>
                    <div class="rule-example">
                        Delete & Archive: Delete ‚Üí Move to Archive<br>
                        Flag for Follow-up: Flag ‚Üí Add to Tasks<br>
                        Forward & Archive: Forward ‚Üí Move to Archive
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="rule-card">
                    <div class="rule-title">üè∑Ô∏è Essential Categories</div>
                    <div class="rule-description">Set up these core GTD categories:</div>
                    <div class="rule-example">
                        @Calls (Red) - Phone calls to make<br>
                        @Computer (Blue) - Computer-based tasks<br>
                        @Meetings (Green) - Items to discuss<br>
                        @Waiting (Yellow) - Waiting for responses
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="rule-card">
                    <div class="rule-title">üîî Notification Settings</div>
                    <div class="rule-description">Minimize interruptions with smart settings:</div>
                    <div class="rule-example">
                        Desktop alerts: OFF<br>
                        Sound notification: OFF<br>
                        Envelope icon: OFF<br>
                        VIP notifications: ON (for key contacts only)
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Slide 7: Common Processing Challenges -->
        <div class="slide" id="slide7">
            <h2>üöß Overcoming Processing Challenges</h2>
            
            <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(350px, 1fr)); gap: 20px; margin: 30px 0;">
                <div style="background: #fef5e7; padding: 20px; border-radius: 10px; border-left: 5px solid #f6ad55;">
                    <h4>üò∞ "I'm Overwhelmed by Volume"</h4>
                    <p><strong>Solution:</strong></p>
                    <ul style="margin: 10px 0;">
                        <li>Start with just today's emails</li>
                        <li>Declare "email bankruptcy" on old emails (archive all)</li>
                        <li>Process for 20 minutes, then stop</li>
                        <li>Focus on building the habit, not perfection</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                
                <div style="background: #f0f9ff; padding: 20px; border-radius: 10px; border-left: 5px solid #3b82f6;">
                    <h4>ü§î "I Can't Decide What to Do"</h4>
                    <p><strong>Solution:</strong></p>
                    <ul style="margin: 10px 0;">
                        <li>When in doubt, defer (flag for later)</li>
                        <li>Use the 2-minute rule strictly</li>
                        <li>Create templates for common responses</li>
                        <li>Remember: any decision is better than no decision</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                
                <div style="background: #f0fdf4; padding: 20px; border-radius: 10px; border-left: 5px solid #10b981;">
                    <h4>‚è∞ "I Don't Have Time for Processing"</h4>
                    <p><strong>Solution:</strong></p>
                    <ul style="margin: 10px 0;">
                        <li>Start with 10 minutes instead of 20</li>
                        <li>Use mobile for quick triage while commuting</li>
                        <li>Block processing time on your calendar</li>
                        <li>Remember: processing saves more time than it takes</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                
                <div style="background: #fdf2f8; padding: 20px; border-radius: 10px; border-left: 5px solid #ec4899;">
                    <h4>üîÑ "I Keep Checking Email Throughout the Day"</h4>
                    <p><strong>Solution:</strong></p>
                    <ul style="margin: 10px 0;">
                        <li>Set specific email checking times (3x per day max)</li>
                        <li>Close Outlook between processing sessions</li>
                        <li>Use phone airplane mode during focused work</li>
                        <li>Create a "checking email" calendar appointment</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                
                <div style="background: #f5f3ff; padding: 20px; border-radius: 10px; border-left: 5px solid #8b5cf6;">
                    <h4>üì± "Mobile Processing is Clunky"</h4>
                    <p><strong>Solution:</strong></p>
                    <ul style="margin: 10px 0;">
                        <li>Use mobile only for triage (delete, flag, quick replies)</li>
                        <li>Set up swipe actions for common decisions</li>
                        <li>Save complex processing for desktop</li>
                        <li>Focus on capture and quick wins while mobile</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                
                <div style="background: #ecfdf5; padding: 20px; border-radius: 10px; border-left: 5px solid #059669;">
                    <h4>üë• "My Team Doesn't Use This System"</h4>
                    <p><strong>Solution:</strong></p>
                    <ul style="margin: 10px 0;">
                        <li>Use GTD internally, communicate clearly externally</li>
                        <li>Set expectations about response times</li>
                        <li>Lead by example with clear, actionable emails</li>
                        <li>Share benefits you're experiencing</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="takeaway-highlight">
                <strong>Remember:</strong> Every challenge is normal and temporary. The key is consistency, not perfection. Start small and build momentum.
            </div>
        </div>

